The paper discusses a semi-automatic approach for finding references to datasets in social sciences papers, which involves natural language processing techniques such as named entity recognition and information extraction. This suggests that the paper could fall under the Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), or Digital Libraries (cs.DL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with data management and registry, which could also place it under the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) or Databases (cs.DB) sub-categories.
